                "response": {
                  "output": "The `monolail/BDA_11` repository is a structured collection of study materials for the **BDA (Big Data Analysis) Society's 11th cohort**, focusing on **SQL** and **Machine Learning (ML)**.[1]\n\n### **Project Purpose**\nThe repository serves as a centralized archive for weekly lecture materials, exercises, and modeling notes.[1] It is designed to guide students through the fundamentals of database management and the end-to-end process of data analysis and machine learning.[1]\n\n### **Repository Structure**\nThe project is organized into two primary directories corresponding to the two main study tracks:\n\n*   **`/SQL`**: Contains materials related to Database Management Systems (DBMS) and SQL syntax.[1]\n    *   **Focus:** Relational data models, data calculation, and core SQL grammar (Weeks 1–11).\n*[1]   **`/ML`**: Contains materials related to Python-based data analysis and machine learning.\n [1]   *   **Focus:** Python/Pandas basics, data visualization, and univariate/bivariate analysis (Weeks 1–11).\n*  [1] **`README.md`**: Provides a high-level curriculum overview and weekly schedules for both tracks.\n\n##[1]# **Key Components & Curriculum**\n\n| Track | Key Topics Covered |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **SQL** | DB Management Systems, Entity-Relationship Models, Relational Algebra, and Advanced SQL Syntax (5+ weeks of grammar). |\n|[1] **ML** | Python/Pandas review, Visualization, Univariate Analysis (Numerical/Categorical), and Bivariate Analysis (Target-based analysis). |\n\n[1]The repository consists entirely of **Jupyter Notebooks**, indicating a hands-on, code-first approach to learning data science and database querying.[1]\n\nSources:\n[1] GitHub - monolail/BDA_11: BDA학회 SQL 및 ML 모델링 공부 내용 (https://github.com/monolail/BDA_11)"
                }
